              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16993328585580356882">Paranormal books are not my usual go to books when reading, however, after reading RUIN: The Waking, I am hooked. Lucian Bane has this magical way to spin a tale that draws you in from page one. I literally was sitting on the edge of my seat waiting to find out what was going to happen next. This is book one in the series and I loved every minute reading it. The characters are very well developed and you will instantly fall in love with Isadore and Ruin and her crazy antics and banter. This is o</span>
  <span id="freeText16993328585580356882" style="display:none">Paranormal books are not my usual go to books when reading, however, after reading RUIN: The Waking, I am hooked. Lucian Bane has this magical way to spin a tale that draws you in from page one. I literally was sitting on the edge of my seat waiting to find out what was going to happen next. This is book one in the series and I loved every minute reading it. The characters are very well developed and you will instantly fall in love with Isadore and Ruin and her crazy antics and banter. This is one book that I will have no problem reading over and over. A brilliant job well done Mr. Bane. Can't wait to read the rest.</span>
