<div id="review_1051885214" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1051885214" />
    <a title="Michelle ♥ The Romance Vault ♥ " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault"><img alt="Michelle ♥ The Romance Vault ♥ " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1388764608p2/7183173.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1051885214?book_show_action=true">Sep 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michelle ♥ The Romance Vault ♥ " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michelle ♥ The Romance Vault ♥ " href="/user/show/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault">Michelle ♥ The Romance Vault ♥ </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=arc-received-publisher-send">arc-received-publisher-send</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=engaging">engaging</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=erotic">erotic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=excellent-supporting-cast">excellent-supporting-cast</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=really-enjoyable">really-enjoyable</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=favourite-series">favourite-series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=favourite-reads-2014">favourite-reads-2014</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7183173-michelle-the-romance-vault?shelf=captivating-read">captivating-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1051885214" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2363063783220270825">Well I really didn’t know what to expect going into this, I haven’t read a Lucian Bane book before and to be honest I haven’t read a paranormal book in a while and this reminded me to make sure I get to read them more often.<br/><br/>This was such a scenic book, it was so easy to place the swamp, the canoe (I know why the canoe! But it is what it is lo and it’s in my head!) Isadore’s kitchen, literally everything was very visual and really played out in my head. Lucian has a delightful way with words and </span>
  <span id="freeText2363063783220270825" style="display:none">Well I really didn’t know what to expect going into this, I haven’t read a Lucian Bane book before and to be honest I haven’t read a paranormal book in a while and this reminded me to make sure I get to read them more often.<br /><br />This was such a scenic book, it was so easy to place the swamp, the canoe (I know why the canoe! But it is what it is lo and it’s in my head!) Isadore’s kitchen, literally everything was very visual and really played out in my head. Lucian has a delightful way with words and yeah some might squirm at the use of the word delightful, but I’m struggling for another way to describe his prose. It isn’t wordy, it isn’t flowery, it’s just very lucid to follow whilst it be very descriptive without endless paragraphs of unwanted drivel. I loved his writing style.<br /><br />I have to say I loved Ruin aka JD as he learns the language and then learns it again the Isadore way, ☺ both of their characters talked to me and befriended me and I found this book really hard to put down once I had delved into their world. I also loved Isadore’s quirkiness.<br /><br />I was quite simply surprised to have liked this as much as I did and I thank Lucian profusely for writing a paranormal romance like this one. It’s sexy, it’s engaging and I could almost feel the heat emanate from Ruin as he struggles to deal with Isadore’s emotions, and as he learns what his own body is telling him.<br /><br />I truly loved it and I am so pleased to have signed up for Ruin’s tour. I received a copy of Ruin in return for an honest review; my reviews are my own and are 100% honest.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2363063783220270825" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


